  "response": "Following the demonetization announcement in November 2016, there was significant debate and disruption in Parliament. Opposition parties strongly criticized the policy and demanded a response from the Prime Minister.\n\nWhile Prime Minister Modi did attend Parliament during the demonetization period, his presence was intermittent. The government's position was often presented by the Finance Minister and other designated ministers.\n\nNews reports and analyses at the time suggested several reasons for the Prime Minister's limited attendance:\n\n*   **Government Strategy:** Some argued that the government strategically chose to have other ministers lead the response in Parliament.\n*   **Focus on Implementation:** Others suggested that the Prime Minister was focused on overseeing the implementation of the demonetization policy and managing its effects on the economy.\n*   **Parliamentary Disruption:** The intense disruptions and protests in Parliament made it difficult to conduct normal business.\n\nIt's worth noting that the specific reasons for the Prime Minister's attendance patterns were subject to political debate and interpretation at the time.",
